news.title: Table Space leases over 5.4 lakh sq ft workspaces across NCR
news.para: Table Space has significantly expanded its presence in the NCR, leasing over 5.4 lakh sq ft of office space. New centers have been established in Delhi's Aerocity and multiple locations in Gurugram, boosting the company's NCR portfolio to over 2.2 million sq ft and adding more than 3,000 ready-to-move-in seats.

news.title: Jaipur smart city to replicate model in six more towns in Rajasthan
news.para: Jaipur Smart City Limited, struggling with its own unfinished projects, has been tasked with developing six new cities. Despite significant investment, many of Jaipur's smart city initiatives remain incomplete or neglected, raising concerns about the expanded mandate. Maintenance issues and a lack of visible 'smart' features plague completed projects.

news.title: Rajasthan: RIICO offers 6,000 plots under direct allotment scheme
news.para: RIICO has launched the sixth phase of its direct allotment scheme for investors who signed MoUs during the Rising Rajasthan Global Investment Summit. This phase offers 6,000 industrial plots across 100 areas until October 14, with special reservations for various categories.

news.title: About 20,000 villagers hold protest against formation of Himmatnagar development body
news.para: Thousands of villagers in Sabarkantha district are protesting the proposed Himmatnagar Urban Development Authority. They demand the scrapping of the notification, citing the acquisition of agricultural land from 11 villages. The protest has been ongoing for 40 days. Villagers have issued a 15-day ultimatum to the government. They plan an indefinite fast if their demands are not met.

news.title: Rising population in cities pose challenge for urbanisation: Housing minister
news.para: Union Minister Manohar Lal Khattar recently convened with leaders from southern states to address the escalating issue of urban growth. Key discussions revolved around improving vital infrastructure like roads, drainage, and metro systems.

news.title: Redevelopment won’t rob anybody of residence rights: West Bengal CM
news.para: Kolkata's Chief Minister Mamata Banerjee reassured residents of old buildings. Redevelopment will protect their rights. She urged traders to reduce plastic use to prevent fires. The Chief Minister also inaugurated a project to shift electric wires underground. A similar project is planned for Kolkata. Grievances against port authorities are being addressed.

news.title: Strict action against PGs and hostels without licences in Bengaluru
news.para: According to the BECC, a large number of PG accommodations and hostels are functioning in violation of civic norms and safety regulations.

news.title: ED attaches assets worth ₹110 crore of Rohtas group
news.para: The Enforcement Directorate has provisionally attached immovable properties worth Rs 110.05 crore in Lucknow, linked to a money laundering case involving Rohtas Project Limited. The probe, initiated based on 83 FIRs, revealed promoters allegedly diverted buyer funds to purchase land through associate entities, defrauding hundreds of investors.

news.title: SC stays GST demand on real estate joint development pacts
news.para: In a pivotal ruling, the Supreme Court has granted a temporary reprieve against a Goods and Services Tax demand related to a joint development agreement for a real estate project. This judicial decision may reshape the landscape for developers and landowners across the country.

news.title: Promoter submits fresh ₹18,000 crore plan for Jaiprakash Associates
news.para: The promoter of Jaiprakash Associates has submitted a new ₹18,000 crore plan to regain control of the company. This offer surpasses those from Vedanta and Adani. Lenders are evaluating the bids, with a vote expected next month. Funding certainty for the promoter's upfront payment remains a key concern for creditors.

news.title: Gurugram civic body seals multi-storey building in Jharsa over unpaid property tax
news.para: Gurugram Municipal Corporation has sealed a residential building for defaulting on Rs 67 lakh in property tax. This action is part of an ongoing drive against major defaulters to boost civic amenities. Officials have collected over Rs 261 crore so far and plan to intensify sealing campaigns to recover outstanding taxes from all property owners.

news.title: DM orders FIR against apartment owners' association of Ghaziabad highrise over financial irregularities
news.para: Ghaziabad District Magistrate Ravindra Mandar ordered an FIR against office-bearers of a Rajnagar Extension society's AOA following a resident's complaint of financial irregularities. An audit revealed discrepancies, prompting the DM to form a special task force to address such complaints and ensure accountability in housing society management.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Popular Builders' owner gets four years in jail
news.para: Popular Builders owner Raman Patel has been convicted and sentenced to four years imprisonment for fraudulent land transactions in Chekhla village. The JMFC court in Sanand found Patel guilty of forgery and criminal conspiracy, imposing a Rs 1.40 lakh fine. The conviction stems from allegations of forging documents to grab ancestral land belonging to a farmer.

news.title: NCLAT rejects UCO Bank claim in Bulland Buildtech insolvency case
news.para: The NCLAT ruled that home loans disbursed by UCO Bank to buyers are not a financial debt of developer Bulland Buildtech. Upholding NCLT orders, the tribunal dismissed UCO Bank's plea to be a financial creditor in the developer's insolvency case. Tripartite agreements did not create repayment obligations for the builder.

news.title: Housing minister seeks details of action against builders not completing projects after three extensions
news.para: Housing Minister Manohar Lal Khattar has demanded details on delayed realty projects and actions against developers. This follows concerns over missed deadlines despite RERA registration. Khattar also called for central vetting of state rules and action against banks mismanaging escrow accounts.

news.title: Lodha Developers' net profit rises 86.67% in Q2 FY26
news.para: Lodha Developers announced a significant profit jump of 86.67 percent for the quarter ending September 30, 2025. The company's profit after tax reached ₹789.80 crore. Total income also saw a substantial increase of 44.49 percent. Lodha Developers achieved its full-year business development goal early. The company is on track to meet its pre-sales guidance.

news.title: DLF's net profit dips 14.56% in Q2 FY26
news.para: DLF reported a 14.56% dip in net consolidated profit for Q2 FY26, with profit after tax at ₹1,180.09 crore. The company's total income saw a 3.71% growth, reaching ₹2,261.80 crore. During the quarter, DLF Home Developers redeemed NCDs and the company declared a dividend of ₹6 per equity share.

news.title: Maharashtra charity commissioner orders cancellation of deed to sell Jain trust property to builder
news.para: Pune's charity commissioner has cancelled the sale of a prime 3.5 acre property. The land, owned by a Jain trust, was to be sold to a builder. The community protested the deal. The builder and trust agreed to cancel the sale deed. The builder will receive a full refund. The property currently houses a boarding and a Jain Temple.

news.title: Crafting the future of luxury living
news.para: Set against the vibrant and dynamic backdrop of a rapidly evolving urban landscape, the grand launch of Jade County symbolised a significant new chapter in contemporary and sustainable residential development

news.title: DDA, IIT-Delhi to inspect 'structural incident' in Dwarka's apartment building
news.para: In response to the unsettling explosion-like noise reported at Triveni Apartments in Dwarka, the Delhi Development Authority has teamed up with IIT-Delhi to conduct a thorough investigation. Specialists will delve into the structural integrity of the building, aiming to pinpoint the cause of the disturbance.
